    "updated_at": "2015-06-22T12:38:54Z",
    "body": "We may add `Download` APIs like \n\n```\ndownloads.download({url: \"\", download_dir:\"\", file_name\"\"}, function(error, downloadId) {})\ndownloads.pause(downloadId, callback)\ndownloads.resume(downloadId, callback)\ndownloads.cancel(downloadId, callback)\ndownloads.show(downloadId)\n\n// details = {\n//   download_id: \"\",\n//   url: \"\",\n//   file_name: \"\",\n//   total_bytes: \"\",\n//   downloaded_bytes:\"\"\n// }\ndownloads.on('changed', function(details) {})\n```\n\nBut I wonder it's worthy adding this. Not sure whether it's a desirable feature that most developers need. \n"
